      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes established benchmark problems (lid-driven cavity, Poiseuille flow) with errors below 1% of analytical solution at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Code verification benchmarks including lid-driven cavity flow at Re=1000 and Hagen-Poiseuille channel flow were executed. Numerical errors were within 0.4% of analytical solutions, satisfying Gradation 2 requirements. Published ANSYS verification documentation supplements internal runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for hemolysis index QoI across three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed (coarse: 4.2M, medium: 11.7M, fine: 31.4M cells). Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI values of 3.1% for the scalar stress-weighted hemolysis index at the worst-case 6 LPM / 3500 RPM operating point. Achieved level exceeds the MRL 2 requirement, providing additional confidence margin."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, outlet pressure, blood analog viscosity, temperature) are documented and matched to CFD inputs within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Experimental conditions from the FDA benchmark dataset (Hariharan et al. 2011) are fully documented. Inlet flow rates were controlled to ±0.05 LPM; temperature maintained at 37±0.5°C. CFD boundary conditions replicate these within measurement uncertainty, satisfying Gradation 2 test-condition correspondence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) agrees with experimental measurements within ±20% across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions at all five flow-speed combinations fall within 14% of experimental measurements from the FDA interlaboratory study. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion is satisfied at the worst-case operating point (6 LPM / 3500 RPM, RH = 0.87). Gradation 2 output comparison requirements are met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, shear stress distribution) are directly linked to the COU decision quantity (relative hemolysis index RH).",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis and volume-averaged scalar shear stress are the primary QoIs. Both are mechanistically linked to the power-law hemolysis model driving the RH acceptance criterion. Relevance is confirmed by the COU definition and the regulatory precedent established in FDA's 2017 computational fluid dynamics guidance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments use the same device geometry, blood analog fluid, and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — identical to the COU device. Glycerol-water blood analog (viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) and the 2–8 LPM / 2500–4500 RPM operating envelope match COU conditions. Geometric and flow similarity is confirmed, satisfying Gradation 2 relevance requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence of residuals to below 1e-5 for all transported quantities, confirmed at each of the five operating points.",
      "rationale": "A comprehensive qualitative assessment of numerical solver error was performed by the credibility assessment team. Residual histories for continuity, momentum, and turbulence transport equations were reviewed across all five operating points. The team determined through expert judgment that solver convergence behavior was consistent with established best practices for rotating-frame turbomachinery simulations, and that no anomalous residual stagnation or divergence patterns were present. The assessment considered the complexity of the SST k-omega turbulence closure in the rotating reference frame, the adequacy of under-relaxation factors employed, and the sufficiency of iteration counts relative to problem stiffness. On the basis of this holistic qualitative review, the solver error contribution was judged to be negligible relative to other identified error sources and does not compromise the overall credibility determination."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup is reviewed by a second qualified analyst prior to result extraction; setup checklist completed and archived.",
      "rationale": "A peer-review checklist covering boundary condition assignment, material property input, rotating domain interface specification, and post-processing scripts was completed and signed off by a second CFD analyst independent of the primary analyst. No setup errors were identified. Gradation 1 use-error controls are satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection is justified by comparison against experimental velocity profiles; hemolysis power-law model coefficients are sourced from peer-reviewed literature.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence closure was selected based on its established performance for swirling flows in rotodynamic devices. Velocity profile comparisons with PIV data from the FDA benchmark study show agreement within 8% in the impeller passage. Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model coefficients (C=1.8×10-6, α=0.765, β=2.416) are taken from Heuser & Opitz (1980) as cited in the FDA guidance. Model form uncertainty is within Gradation 2 tolerance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood analog fluid properties and pump geometry dimensions are documented with traceability to measurement records; sensitivity of NIH to ±5% variation in viscosity is quantified.",
      "rationale": "Fluid properties (density 1056 kg/m³, dynamic viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) are traceable to rheometer calibration records. Pump geometry was imported from FDA-released CAD files with dimensional verification against published drawings. A one-at-a-time sensitivity study showed NIH varies by less than 3% for ±5% viscosity perturbation, confirming input uncertainty is within Gradation 2 tolerance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental hemolysis measurements include at least three independent repeat runs per operating point with reported standard deviation.",
      "rationale": "The FDA interlaboratory dataset provides measurements from multiple independent laboratories using the same pump geometry. Repeat measurements within each laboratory (minimum n=3) are reported with standard deviations. The resulting experimental uncertainty band is used directly in the output comparison assessment. Gradation 1 test-sample requirements are satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD model input parameters (rotational speed, flow rate, fluid viscosity) match experimental conditions within ±2% for each of the five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Rotational speeds and volumetric flow rates applied as CFD boundary conditions are matched to experimental setpoints within 0.8% and 1.1% respectively across all five operating points. Fluid viscosity equivalency is confirmed by the rheometer records referenced under Model Inputs. Equivalency of input parameters is demonstrated at Gradation 2."
    }
